      <p>I FINALLY made these cookies last night and they are so good! I&#8217;m glad I had the self control to put them in a container until today because their flavor definitely improved. They&#8217;re my new favorite, for sure. Thanks for the recipe!</></>I mentioned it in my blog post today and sited you and your blog:</><a href="http://onehungrysoul.blogspot.com/2009/01/no-ordinary-cookie.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://onehungrysoul.blogspot.com/2009/01/no-ordinary-cookie.html</a></p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-9718" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.drugrehab-oklahoma.org" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">amy</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/12/the-cookie-baking-part/#comment-9718"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-10-20T20:12:44-04:00">Tuesday, October 20, 2009 at 8:12 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love to bake however with me working at <a href="http://www.drugrehab-oklahoma.org" rel="nofollow">Narconon</a> drug rehab facility and being a single mother I have very little time to bake. If anyone has any ideas on quick cookie ideas let me know.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-9719" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/07494903685761888166" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Aria</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/12/the-cookie-baking-part/#comment-9719"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-12-14T23:42:47-05:00">Monday, December 14, 2009 at 11:42 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I&#39;ve been dying to make these cookies. I need to make some &#8220;asian inspired&#8221; cookies for a big event this week. How do you think these would be with a little candied ginger thrown in with the cocoa nibs?</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-9720" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/12/the-cookie-baking-part/#comment-9720"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-12-15T00:51:52-05:00">Tuesday, December 15, 2009 at 12:51 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Aria, I don&#39;t think I would put candied ginger in these.  I think it would overpower the delicate flavor of the buckwheat, and I don&#39;t know, I&#39;m just afraid it wouldn&#39;t taste <i>good</i>, you know?</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-9721" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/lisasteinbrueck/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Lisa</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/12/the-cookie-baking-part/#comment-9721"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-09-24T02:19:31-04:00">Saturday, September 24, 2011 at 2:19 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>So this week we got a (beautiful) new (to us) fridge, and yesterday we finished transferring everything from the old to the new. And in the back of our old freezer I found a quarter log of these cookies! I do not remember when we made them &#8212; praying it was not actually 2007. I&#39;m testing their mettle by baking them up now.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-9722" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/lisasteinbrueck/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Lisa</a></cite></div>
